description.plain:
Saweetie is an American rapper and songwriter hailing from Hayward, California. She was born Diamonté Quiava Valentin Harper on July 2nd, 1993, and was largely raised in the Bay Area but finished high school in Sacramento.

Harper grew up listening to the likes of 2Pac, Biggie and Lil Kim and first started performing in high school at a talent show during Black History Month. She would later go on to perform covers of other artists' hit songs, such as A$AP Rocky’s “F**kin' Problems,” during her time at the University of Southern California, where she studied communications and business.

After graduating, Saweetie started to focus more on her rap career. – She finally burst onto the rap scene in 2017, when an Instagram clip of the rapper performing her freestyle “ICY GIRL” went viral. The studio release of the track has since  accumulated more than 126 million streams across all platforms. – In June 2018, the single was certified Gold after selling over 500,000 units in the US.

On March 16th, 2018, Saweetie released her highly-anticipated debut EP High Maintenance after signing to Warner Bros. Records in February of the same year. The record features production from the rapper’s cousin, veteran producer Zaytoven.

It was around that time, too, that Harper started dating Atlanta native and Migos‘ member Quavo. She would later be featured on the rapper’s 2018 solo album Quavo Huncho.

Almost exactly one year after the release of her debut, Saweetie dropped her sophomore EP, ICY, on March 29th, 2019. The project boasts only one feature, Quavo, who has two appearances on the record.

songs.title: Best Friend

description.plain:
“Best Friend,” the first collaboration between Saweetie and Doja Cat, was prematurely released by her own label on Apple Music and Deezer on 4 December 2020, a month before the scheduled release. The song serves as the third single for Saweetie’s upcoming debut album, Pretty Bitch Music.

Shortly after it hit streaming services, the rapper called out Warner Records to express the frustration and disappointment she experienced over the accident.


I feel disrespected. I’m hands on with ALL of my creative & had such a dope rollout for ‘best friends’.

We put so much work into the visual & we shot for days for this super cinematic girl anthem. And for this to happen? Wow….

songs.title: My Type

description.plain:
Another viral hit from California’s finest, Saweetie released “My Type” on her album Icy on March 29th 2019. The song taps into nostalgia with a sample of the 2004 “Freek-A-Leek” by Petey Pablo.

Adding fuel to her fire, Saweetie released her “My Type” video featuring appearances by the cast members of TNT’s television show “Claws” In the video, you can spot fan-favorites Karrueche, Niecy Nash and Carrie Preston.
